<TITLE> Razzaq visits Hatia, oversees relief ops </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May29 (bdnews24.com)The food and disaster management minister Abdur Razzaq visited the cyclonic Aila-hit Hatia Upazila of Noakhali on Friday to see the condition of the affected people. During his tour, he visited the shelter centres at Karing Char, Boyrar Char primary school and Bangabandhu School field and distributed relief materials among the affected people. Later, the minister visited other affected areas in the Upazila. Razzaq said the government stood by the affected people with adequate relief materials. Huge relief materials had already been distributed and more would be allocated, if necessary, he said The minister cautioned the relief distributors with dire consequences over any irregularities or corruption. Local MP Mohammad Ali and officials of local administrations were with him during the visit. b
